{"schema_version": 2, "ts": "2026-05-11T00:00:00Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "reduce-boot-context-surface-claudemd-skillmd", "parent_epic_loaded": true, "findings": [{"text": "Intent clarity HIGH rests on 'measurable reduction' but the source defers the target number ('specific number set during research after measurement'); the acceptance signal is also compound (token reduction AND routing parity AND conditional CLAUDE.md/CHANGELOG clauses).", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Intent clarity HIGH ignores the load-bearing unresolved empirical question: the largest lever (trigger-phrase-move, ~2,300 tok) is gated on whether the loader routes against non-`description` frontmatter, which the source itself flags as currently unknown.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Scope boundedness HIGH cites Out-of-scope but the Out-of-scope clause excludes the empirical loader test, while Research-hook #2 (trigger-phrase move) requires that test — a direct contradiction in the source.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Scope boundedness HIGH conflates 'levers enumerated' with 'scope bounded' — actual lever selection is research-driven.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Scope boundedness HIGH does not engage with the CLAUDE.md 100-line rule's self-referential constraint: the CLAUDE.md-extraction lever requires changing the rule that governs the lever.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Requirements alignment HIGH is wrong: CLAUDE.md's policy mandates extraction only when a new entry would push past 100 lines; current state is 67/100, so preemptive extraction conflicts with the as-written project policy.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Requirements alignment HIGH does not engage with whether relocating the MUST-escalation policy itself triggers the policy's own evidence requirement.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Complexity 'complex' undercounts: the work potentially requires research-infrastructure (loader test, invocation-frequency telemetry, snapshot test replacement, rule reframing, CHANGELOG).", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Criticality 'high' was defaulted from the protocol; the silent-routing-regression risk on always-on infrastructure with an inadequate test gate arguably warrants 'critical'.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Existing snapshot test (tests/test_skill_descriptions.py) is treated as a sufficient guard, but the largest proposed lever (trigger-phrase move) defeats the test's coverage by design.", "origin": "primary"}], "dispositions": {"apply": 3, "dismiss": 6, "ask": 1}, "applied_fixes": ["Sharpened the clarified intent statement to: 'Evaluate the enumerated boot-context-reduction levers (description compression, trigger-phrase move, skill consolidation/deletion, SKILL.md body trimming, CLAUDE.md policy extraction) and commit during spec to the subset that delivers measurable always-on token reduction without skill-routing regression. Intent clarity remains HIGH — direction and constraint surface are crisp; deferred-target is a feature of research-driven specs.", "Added an open question for research: 'Treat the empirical loader-routing test (out-of-scope per the ticket) as effectively excluded — so research must rely on Anthropic-documented behavior or fall back to compression-only for trigger-phrase content; flag this for explicit user decision in spec.'", "Downgraded requirements alignment from HIGH to 'Partial alignment: aligned with project.md workflow-trimming doctrine (line 23) and complexity-earns-its-place (line 19), but conflicts with CLAUDE.md's 100-line extraction trigger (current state 67/100; preemptive extraction is not authorized by the as-written rule). The ticket folds rule-reframing into scope; user must confirm during spec that they accept reframing the rule alongside extraction.'"], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Research-driven lever selection is the standard refine pattern (research evaluates, spec commits). The set of candidate levers IS enumerated and bounded — that's what scope-boundedness measures."}, {"finding_index": 4, "rationale": "The CLAUDE.md 100-line rule self-reference is explicitly acknowledged in the ticket's Constraints section and the rule-reframing is folded into the Acceptance signal — scope is nested but bounded."}, {"finding_index": 6, "rationale": "Relocation is not addition or restoration of MUST language; the policy's evidence requirement governs new escalations. The grandfathering clause ('pre-existing MUST language is grandfathered until specifically audited per #85') applies."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "Complexity is already at the top binary tier ('complex'); cited additional surface does not change the binary classification."}, {"finding_index": 8, "rationale": "Per the lifecycle clarify protocol, CRITICAL is reserved for severe consequences (security, data loss, financial, or loss of a core capability). Routing-degradation for some triggers is severe-user-impact but does not meet CRITICAL's protocol-defined bar — degraded UX, not loss-of-capability."}, {"finding_index": 9, "rationale": "The ticket already imposes the equivalent-guardrail constraint on any lever that defeats the existing test ('keep this test passing or replace it with an equivalent guardrail against the new surface'). The constraint is in the source; the assessment does not need to re-derive it."}], "status": "ok"}
